le Blade</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 12:07:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jakefitch.com/eq/images/mil_wf.gif width=60 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> Enough of the bickering.  Here is a proposal, in 2 parts, please vote ya/nay for each part.<br>
<br>
A.  If the posting entity in the plane knows they can not kill the god before the 2am PST deadline they must call in the Epic/BB guild before 9pm PST.  If the call for the BB/Epic guild does not occur by 9pm PST then the responsiblity of the god dieing falls upon the shoulders of the posting entity in the plane that night.<br>
<br>
B.  If an Epic/BB guild is called in to kill a god, the 2am PST ending time shall be extended to 4am PST.<br>
<br>
Penalties for leaving a god up will be discussed in another thread. <p>Milambus Mandragon<BR>
Noble Blade<BR>
The Rathe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthorfinnwayforger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorfinn Wayforger</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Requiem of Souls</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 12:32:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> Simple, easy to understand, no real room for interpretation... I like Simple.<br>
<br>
A: Yes<br>
B: Yes<br>
<br>
Thorfinn Wayforger<br>
RoS Guild Leader <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustygar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stygar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Clan Icewind Guild Leader</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 12:35:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqraid.org/images/characters/qwaifitz2.gif width=130 height=98></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of Nyca's. The guild that is up, should be able to tell if they will kill the God when they start the raid. Or the BB guild gets a tentative notification when they start. I think 9 is too late, especially if BB is doing something else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umilambus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milambus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Blade</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 12:52:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jakefitch.com/eq/images/mil_wf.gif width=60 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> Qwai,<br>
<br>
I agree with Nycah's idea as well.  Its too bad the BB guilds havn't been doing that isn't it?  <br>
<br>
And the fact that 2 out of the last 3 guilds &quot;thought&quot; they could take CT down.<br>
<br>
I really wish we didn't need more rules, because they confuse things, but they seem to be needed.<br>
<br>
Nycah's idea is something that is solely within the grasp of the BB up on rotation, new rules are something the calendar as a system can do.<br>
<br>
So, as a person who believes the system as a whole is good, and thinks it in general works, I am taking what steps I can to see the system work.  I can not control whether the BB guild contacts the scheduled raiding parties.  I can only try to modify the system such that if they do not make that contact the system can work around it. <p>Milambus Mandragon<BR>
Noble Blade<BR>
The Rathe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Glossolalia/CTA</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 12:54:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> If the god is up, and the big brother guild knows it, they shouldn't be doing anything else that night but waiting on call.  Setting the notify time to 9pm gives you five hours from notification to clear the plane.  And how about the epic guild handling the initial communication?  Since the epics have done such a craptastic job of handling their rotation information, it's VERY difficult for anyone to know precisely who is up, sometimes.<br>
<br>
If you want to do something else that night, notify the next in line for the notification, and bump yourself to the bottom of the list.<br>
<br>
Don't like the idea of being bumped to the bottom of the list?  Make sure you're ready to go in at a moment's notice, then.  Your responsibility as an on-call epic guild is to make sure the god dies.  Not to make sure you get god loot with a minimum of hassle on your part.<br>
<br>
If you're a person who works an on-call job, you don't get to say &quot;only do on calls for me from 9pm to midnight.  before that i want to watch tv and the calls might be hard to get to before then.&quot; <br>
<br>
But hey, at least we're talking now, and 'FFA' isn't in every other sentence. heh.<br>
<br>
How about all the epic guilds get reps in game tonight and have a meeting to hash out what the epic guilds want to do for handling rotation/rules/punishment/etc.<br>
<br>
I've only been suggesting that for, like, a week.<br>
<br>
Because if the epic guilds can't be civil to each other long enough to come up with an agreeable set of rules for the epic rotation system, then that part of the calendar is doomed, and we may as well just make it an 'FYI' list for guilds to notify and pull up Big Brother to take down a god.<br>
<br>
Bias &quot;I won't make a proposal, it's not my place&quot; Schmias <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthorfinnwayforger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorfinn Wayforger</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Requiem of Souls</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 1:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> This kinda brings up the &quot;responsibility&quot; of being an Epic guild. If you are up, and so is the god... You shouldn't BE &quot;doing something else&quot;. This responsibility is one of the driving reasons that RoS will decline to become &quot;Epic&quot; when we qualify (which we will eventually, probably very soon). We don't want to be tied down whenever it's our turn, and a god is up. We don't want to have the responsibility of having enough people on and ready to go in and kill Cazic at a moment's notice, with little time. The benefit of getting the epic loot just isn't worth the hassle. Yes, we have many people waiting on that epic loot to finish their quests, but we'll wait our turn...<br>
<br>
Perhaps some of the current guilds need to reevaluate whether they really want that responsibility... Because, in accepting the &quot;Epic&quot; title, you do assume that responsibility.<br>
<br>
Thorfinn Wayforger<br>
RoS Guild Leader <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzachtonsoulstriker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZachtonSoulstriker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Slavedriver</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 2:10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://jpsexton.tripod.com/zachton.jpg height=131 width=175></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> Just a question, what should the penalty be for failing to calling in the BB guild?  Also should it be a hard nosed botom line penalty or should it be discused on this board if it was truly their fault (server lag, dumps that night, etc..) <p>Zachton Soulstriker <br>56 Templar of Karana <br> Xach Soulstriker <br> 26 Ranger of Karana <br> Zachrot Hasissues <br> 21 Paladin of Brell <br> Master of life for Requiem of Souls of the Rathe.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkoak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOak</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Slavedriver</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 3:52:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> Server lag.. bah.. it's server-wide lag.. you can cope with it or die trying.. speaking of which.. doubtful anyone could survive several of the lovely ones I've been a part of the last day or so.<br>
