GM DBN <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustygar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stygar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Clan Icewind Guild Leader</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 8:36:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqraid.org/images/characters/qwaifitz2.gif width=130 height=98></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> I think 8pm pst, 11pm est is late enough to know if you will kill the God. <br>
<br>
Why not get a list of entities that have actually killed a God. If the guild who is up, has not killed the God, let BB send as many as need from the start. The less experienced guild would then learn from people who &quot;should&quot; know what they are doing.<br>
<br>
The BB guild that is up, should take initiative to get in touch with the guild in the plane. Verify that they can, or cannot kill the God, then notify the Admins of the situation. <br>
<br>
This should make a 2am finish very achievable.<br>
2am will be documented as the end of a raid no matter what. If the BB does not get the kill within that time frame, the next BB  is up. No excuses. Server drops, tough luck, those are the breaks. <br>
<br>
<br>
New rule: BB can NOT be called in the day before they have a Plane.. We can call this the FR rule.<br>
<br>
New rule: BB can not be in the plane on God days if a capable guild is in the Plane. If a BB member has a trade arranged, he will wait outside till the God is dead.<br>
<br>
New rule: Sky will support Fri/Sat raids for people going to the top. Sat/Sun raids for people staying below. The Admins will determine if you are capable to reserve Friday starts.<br>
<br>
New rule: Anyone breaking the rules will lose 1 raid on 1st offense. 2nd offense 45 days no posting rights. 3rd offense banned from The Rathe calendar for 90 days.<br>
<br>
Entities must be held accountable for breaking the rules. If not then we cannot have a Calendar.<br>
<br>
We need to have a rules enforcement commitee. Need some ideas on who should be on this commitee. Maybe 50+ member entities get 1 rep?<br>
<br>
I think I have covered most sticking points in getting this agreement done. <br>
<br>
Notice I did NOT use the F word! HAHA.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujairnreiynon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jairn Reiy non</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Breed of Norrath</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/5/01 9:27:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal: BB Guild Call in Time</span><hr size=1> Finally some headway.  I think all guild reps should post their &quot;rules&quot; they want included here.  Stygar has quite a few up that have been talked about so I will give input on them.<br>
<br>
8pm PST to call in BB.  Works for me.<br>
<br>
List of guilds who have killed CT.  Works for me but when that guild that hasn't killed CT wants to take their shot &quot;realistically&quot; then we let em do it.<br>
<br>
Communication is key to any raid.  BB up should be the one to initiate the talks.<br>
<br>
2am finish time is fine with me.  (one possible problem--server crash after the call in time.  BB gets called in at say 11pm PST after a server crash.  Should we give them a flat out 4 hours? 5?  Should the god stay up for the next days raid?)  Also how strict are we going to be with this.  Is 1 minute over punishable?(clocks all are off more then that in my house alone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  Is 5 minutes?  Is 10?  We need input here.<br>
<br>
